  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Gurjaani Hog Enterprise Development Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will be implemented in the village Gurjanni of Gurjaani municipality, East Georgia. In partnership with the Gurjaani Farmers Association Alazani, the project will directly assist 230 families through the development of hog farming in the community. In the first two years of the project, Heifer will provide 40 families with 40 gilts. During the lifespan of the project, an additional 190 families will benefit from nine Passing on the Gift cycles. In addition to gilts and fodder, all participants will receive training on advanced farm and animal management, as well as technical assistance and veterinary medicines to establish and run their own small-scale hog farms. The Gurjaani Farmers Association Alazani members&#x2019; contributions to the project will be the renovation of an old building, which will be used to shelter the sows; as well as the construction of a water supply system that will lead to the piggery area. Over the course of three years, with the assistance of Heifer Georgia, project participants will create a hog enterprise and improve their community&#x2019;s food security and nutritional level through pork production and consumption, as well as increase their incomes through the rearing of sows and the sale of piglets and pork on the market.</narrative>
  </description>
